YOUR RIGHT
Rights of EEU Residents We process and respond to your requests without unnecessary delay, typically within one month of receiving the request. However, if the request is complex, we may take up to three months to respond, as permitted by Article 12 of the GDPR.
Right to Access
You have the right to request access to the data we process about you, as outlined in Article 15 of the GDPR. This includes details such as:
The purpose of the data processing.
The types of personal data involved.
The recipients or categories of recipients of the data.
The expected retention period for the personal data.
You are also entitled to receive a copy of the personal data we process. Note that access may be restricted due to intellectual property or trade secrets.
Right to Object
You can object to our processing of your personal data if it is based on the balancing of interests rule under Article 6(1)(f) of the GDPR, as per Article 21. If you object, we will stop processing unless we have legitimate reasons that override your rights or the processing is necessary for legal claims.
You can also object to the processing of your personal data for direct marketing at any time, and we will stop processing your data for this purpose.
Right to Rectification
You have the right to have any inaccurate personal data corrected, as per Article 16 of the GDPR.
Right to Restriction
You may request the restriction of your personal data processing in specific circumstances, as outlined in Article 18 of the GDPR. If granted, we will only process your data with your consent or for legal reasons, such as to protect a person or for the public interest.
Right to Withdraw Consent
If we have requested your consent for data processing, you can withdraw it at any time under Article 7 of the GDPR. Once withdrawn, we will stop processing the relevant data, unless legally required to retain parts of it. Withdrawing consent does not affect the legality of data processing carried out before the withdrawal.
Right to Data Portability
You have the right to receive the personal data you provided to us in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format. You can also request the transfer of this data to another controller if the processing is based on consent or contract performance, as per Article 20 of the GDPR.
Rights of California Residents
We aim to respond to verifiable consumer requests within 45 days. If more time is needed (up to 90 days), we will inform you in writing. Any disclosures will cover the 12 months prior to the request, and we will explain any reasons for non-compliance. For data portability requests, we will provide your data in a format that allows easy transmission to another entity.
Right to Opt-Out
Under the CCPA, California residents can request that businesses stop selling their personal information to third parties.
Right to be Informed
You have the right to know what categories of personal data we collect and the purpose of its collection. This information is provided in our Privacy Policy, which is updated at least annually.
Right to Disclosure
You can request disclosure of the personal data we have collected on you within the past 12 months. Our Privacy Policy outlines the types of personal data collected, the sources, and how it is used.
Right to Deletion
You may request the deletion of your personal data collected within the last 12 months. However, in some cases, we may be required to retain data for a period, such as to provide services, address security issues, comply with the law, or fulfill other obligations. If no such obligations exist, we will delete your data upon request.
CHANGES
This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time for any reason. The Service Provider will notify you of any changes to the Privacy Policy by updating this page with the new Privacy Policy. You are advised to consult this Privacy Policy regularly for any changes, as continued use is deemed approval of all changes.
